 flourishing. By outlining how state-framed forms of love create desires that cannot be fulfilled, Zhang places China at the forefront of using affective attachments to nation, leader, and family in the global shifts toward exploitation and authoritarianism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunism and lovezChina. 0aGlobalizationzChina. 0aMigration, InternalzChinaxHistory. 0aNationalismzChina. 0aNeoliberalismzChina. 0aRural-urban migrationzChina. 0aSex rolezChina. 0aWomenxEmploymentzChina. 0aWomenzChinaxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aWork and familyxGovernment policyzChina. 0aWork and familyzChina. 0aWork-life balancezChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022619?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022619423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022619/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022